data.summary: [PR Newswire] - BALA CYNWYD, Pa., Jan. 14, 2016 /PRNewswire/ -- Law office of Brodsky & Smith, LLC announces that it is investigating potential claims against the Board of Directors of Anchor Bancorp Wisconsin Inc ("Anchor" or "the Company") (Nasdaq- ABCW-News) for possible breaches of fiduciary duty and other violations of state law in connection with the sale of the Company to Old National Bancorp. Under the terms of the transaction, Anchor shareholders will receive either only $48.50 in cash or 3.5505 shares of ONB for each share of Anchor stock they own. The investigation concerns whether the Board of Anchor breached their fiduciary duties to shareholders and whether ONB is underpaying for the Company.
data.title: SHAREHOLDER ALERT: Brodsky & Smith, LLC Announces Investigation of The Board of Directors of Anchor Bancorp Wisconsin Inc. -ABCW
